           <tr>
            <td class="mbox-image">
             <div class="mbox-image-div">
              <span typeof="mw:File">
               <span>
                <img alt="" class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="40" data-file-width="40" decoding="async" height="40" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/40px-Ambox_important.svg.png" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/60px-Ambox_important.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/80px-Ambox_important.svg.png 2x" width="40"/>
               </span>
              </span>
             </div>
            </td>
            <td class="mbox-text">
             <div class="mbox-text-span">
              <div class="multiple-issues-text mw-collapsible">
               <b>
                This article has multiple issues.
               </b>
               Please help
               <b>
                <a href="/wiki/Special:EditPage/List_of_trees_and_shrubs_by_taxonomic_family" title="Special:EditPage/List of trees and shrubs by taxonomic family">
                 improve it
                </a>
               </b>
               or discuss these issues on the
               <b>
                <a href="/wiki/Talk:List_of_trees_and_shrubs_by_taxonomic_family" title="Talk:List of trees and shrubs by taxonomic family">
                 talk page
                </a>
               </b>
               .

         <p>
          The following is a list of widely known trees and shrubs.
          <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-morton1_1-0">
           <a href="#cite_note-morton1-1">
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             [
            </span>
            1
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             ]
            </span>
           </a>
          </sup>
          <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-arbor1_2-0">
           <a href="#cite_note-arbor1-2">
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             [
            </span>
            2
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             ]
            </span>
           </a>
          </sup>
          <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-usda1_3-0">
           <a href="#cite_note-usda1-3">
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             [
            </span>
            3
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             ]
            </span>
           </a>
          </sup>
          <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-BONMAP1_4-0">
           <a href="#cite_note-BONMAP1-4">
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             [
            </span>
            4
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             ]
            </span>
           </a>
          </sup>
          <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-MBG1_5-0">
           <a href="#cite_note-MBG1-5">
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             [
            </span>
            5
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             ]
            </span>
           </a>
          </sup>
          <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-arnold1_6-0">
           <a href="#cite_note-arnold1-6">
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             [
            </span>
            6
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             ]
            </span>
           </a>
          </sup>
          <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-FNA1_7-0">
           <a href="#cite_note-FNA1-7">
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             [
            </span>
            7
            <span class="cite-bracket">
             ]
            </span>
           </a>
          </sup>
          Taxonomic families for the following trees and shrubs are listed in alphabetical order, likewise the genera and closely related species. The list currently includes 1352 species.
         </p>
